What is yeast?

Yeast is a single-celled fungus. It isn’t trying to make bread or beer. It’s trying to survive and reproduce.

Its metabolism converts sugars into usable energy. Depending on the environment (especially oxygen availability), one consequence is producing carbon dioxide and ethanol.

From a systems perspective:

Environment
      ↓
Gene regulation
      ↓
Metabolism
      ↓
Products

The “program” isn’t rewritten each time; different parts of the organism’s existing capabilities are expressed under different conditions.

